 848: class StateActionGroup(State):
 849:     def moveTo(self):
 850:         State.moveTo(self)
 851: 
 852:         actGp = self.brain.sim.actionGroups[self.settings["GroupName"]]
 853: 
 854:         self.actionName = random.choice(actGp)
 855: 
 856:         act = self.actionName
 857:         if act in self.brain.sim.actions:
 858:             actionobj = self.brain.sim.actions[act]  # from .cm_motion.py
 859:             obj = bpy.context.scene.objects[self.brain.userid]  # bpy object
 860: 
 861:             tr = obj.animation_data.nla_tracks.new()  # NLA track
 862:             action = actionobj.action  # bpy action
 863:             if action:
 864:                 currentFrame = bpy.context.scene.frame_current
 865:                 self.strip = tr.strips.new("", currentFrame, action)
 866:                 self.strip.extrapolation = 'NOTHING'
 867:                 self.strip.use_auto_blend = True
 868:             self.length = actionobj.length
 869: 
 870:     def evaluateState(self):
 871:         self.currentFrame += 1
 872: 
 873:         #Check to see if the current state is still playing an animation
 874:         # The proportion of the way through the state
 875:         if self.length == 0:
 876:             complete = 1
 877:         else:
 878:             complete = self.currentFrame/self.length
 879:             complete = 0.5 + complete/2
 880:         currentFrame = bpy.context.scene.frame_current
 881:         self.resultLog[currentFrame] = ((0.15, 0.4, complete))
 882: 
 883:         if self.actionName in self.brain.sim.actions:
 884:             actionobj = self.brain.sim.actions[self.actionName]
 885: 
 886:             for data_path, data in actionobj.motiondata.items():
 887:                 x = data[0][self.currentFrame] - data[0][self.currentFrame - 1]
 888:                 y = data[1][self.currentFrame] - data[1][self.currentFrame - 1]
 889:                 z = data[2][self.currentFrame] - data[2][self.currentFrame - 1]
 890:                 if data_path == "location":
 891:                     self.brain.outvars["px"] += x
 892:                     self.brain.outvars["py"] += y
 893:                     self.brain.outvars["pz"] += z
 894:                 elif data_path == "rotation_euler":
 895:                     self.brain.outvars["rx"] += x
 896:                     self.brain.outvars["ry"] += y
 897:                     self.brain.outvars["rz"] += z
 898: 
 899:         if self.currentFrame < self.length - 1:
 900:             return False, self.name
 901: 
 902:         # ==== Will stop here is this state hasn't reached its end ====
 903: 
 904:         options = []
 905:         for con in self.outputs:
 906:             val = self.neurons[con].query()
 907:             if val is not None:
 908:                 options.append((con, val))
 909: 
 910:         # If the cycleState button is checked then add a contection back to
 911:         #    this state again.
 912:         if self.cycleState and self.name not in self.outputs:
 913:             val = self.neurons[self.name].query()
 914:             if val is not None:
 915:                 options.append((self.name, val))
 916: 
 917:         if len(options) > 0:
 918:             if len(options) == 1:
 919:                 return True, options[0][0]
 920:             else:
 921:                 return True, max(options, key=lambda v: v[1])[0]
 922: 
 923:         return False, None
